featured_reviews.review_id: This mosque (Sunni Shahi Mosque) is famous by the name of Purani Shahi Masjid Paschim Tola.  This mosque is located in the Paschim Tola Mohalla near Manihari Ganga Ghat.  Every year during the flood, the water of the Ganges river flows touching the foundation of this mosque.  But this mosque has been steadily existing in its place for many years.  This is the reason that makes this mosque special.  This mosque is under the care of the Imam and the local people here.  Around 400 to 500 people reside in Paschim Tola Mohalla, who offer Namaz on their daily basis every day.  The people here are good, friendly and peaceful.  People here have true faith and belief in their religion.  Near this mosque is the "Madrasa Gausia Faizia Najamia", where many children are getting education.  Being on the banks of river Ganges, you can also know it historically.
